OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FLancet study: Pollution    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fkilled 2.3 million Indians 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fin 2019                    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Pollution led to more than 2.3 million 
OL,6, premature deaths in India in 2019,     
OL,7, according to a new Lancet study.       
OL,9,FNearly 1.6 million deaths were due to  
OL,10,Fair pollution alone, and more than     
OL,11,F500,000 were caused by water pollution.
OL,13,FThe latest Lancet Commission on        
OL,14,Fpollution and health report blamed     
OL,15,Fpollution for nine million - or about  
OL,16,Fone in six - deaths globally.          
OL,18,FIt said India - where bad air kills    
OL,19,Fmore than a million people every year -
OL,20,Fremained among the worst affected.     
